155
00:05:49,910 --> 00:05:52,220
Habit four, knowing when to quit.

156
00:05:52,220 --> 00:05:54,760
Now, I know this one
might sound a bit strange.

157
00:05:54,760 --> 00:05:57,200
Quitting is usually seen as a bad thing,

158
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:58,320
but in my experience,

159
00:05:58,320 --> 00:06:00,610
it helped me go from a
carpenter's apprentice

160
00:06:00,610 --> 00:06:03,051
earning less than $2 per hour

161
00:06:03,051 --> 00:06:05,290
to a millionaire by my late 20's.

162
00:06:05,290 --> 00:06:07,750
When I was working that minimum wage job

163
00:06:07,750 --> 00:06:10,890
and I first had an issue
with my manager bullying me,

164
00:06:10,890 --> 00:06:12,030
I could have kept going

165
00:06:12,030 --> 00:06:14,340
and worked my way up
the company gradually,

166
00:06:14,340 --> 00:06:15,910
but I decided to quit.

167
00:06:15,910 --> 00:06:18,250
That led me to starting my own business.

168
00:06:18,250 --> 00:06:21,850
And within a few months I was
drowning in all the paperwork.

169
00:06:21,850 --> 00:06:25,490
So I decided to quit that job
and I hired someone to help.

170
00:06:25,490 --> 00:06:26,500
And before I knew it,

171
00:06:26,500 --> 00:06:29,150
I'd replaced all the jobs
I could with other people.

172
00:06:29,150 --> 00:06:31,450
This allowed me to focus
on being the captain

173
00:06:31,450 --> 00:06:34,210
and steering the business
in the right direction.

174
00:06:34,210 --> 00:06:36,960
The big lesson here is not
to be too proud to quit

175
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:38,480
when you don't like something,

176
00:06:38,480 --> 00:06:41,410
or you feel the effort
is not worth the reward.

177
00:06:41,410 --> 00:06:44,060
I see so many people
struggling at university

178
00:06:44,060 --> 00:06:45,820
and working long days and nights

179
00:06:45,820 --> 00:06:48,600
for a degree they don't actually want.

180
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:50,610
They've just been pushed down that path

181
00:06:50,610 --> 00:06:52,230
by teachers and parents.

182
00:06:52,230 --> 00:06:54,930
Of course this isn't
everyone, but in my opinion,

183
00:06:54,930 --> 00:06:56,880
quitting has its time and place.

184
00:06:56,880 --> 00:07:00,000
And there is no shame in
admitting something isn't for you.

185
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:01,840
This isn't to say that you should quit

186
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:03,450
just because something's hard,

187
00:07:03,450 --> 00:07:06,620
but there has to be a reason
to put in all the hard work.

188
00:07:06,620 --> 00:07:07,860
Don't let others shame you

189
00:07:07,860 --> 00:07:10,040
if you make the hard decision to move on

190
00:07:10,040 --> 00:07:12,140
to bigger and better things.

191
00:07:12,140 --> 00:07:14,900
After all, the opportunity
cost of staying where you are,

192
00:07:14,900 --> 00:07:16,970
could be much greater than you realized.

193
00:07:16,970 --> 00:07:19,110
Just imagine of outside work and as a cop

194
00:07:19,110 --> 00:07:21,320
to making wooden trash cans all my life.

195
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:23,290
Nah, never have happened.

196
00:07:23,290 --> 00:07:25,390
Habit Number five is treating your body

197
00:07:25,390 --> 00:07:27,560
