198
00:07:27,560 --> 00:07:30,220
I know it might be sounding
a bit like a fitness guru,

199
00:07:30,220 --> 00:07:32,950
but as cheesy as it is,
without good health,

200
00:07:32,950 --> 00:07:35,890
you won't be able to unlock
your full earning potential.

201
00:07:35,890 --> 00:07:39,290
I had to relearn this lesson
recently when the pandemic hit.

202
00:07:39,290 --> 00:07:41,010
Lots of my staff were in lockdown,

203
00:07:41,010 --> 00:07:44,730
which meant I decided to
work three months flat out.

204
00:07:44,730 --> 00:07:46,140
I was even in the warehouse

205
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:48,800
packing and shipping
orders with minimal staff,

206
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:50,920
as I didn't want to let my customers down.

207
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:53,190
I actually worked 15 hours a day,

208
00:07:53,190 --> 00:07:56,240
seven days a week, for
three months straight.

209
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:59,600
I got very stressed and started
having lots of migraines.

210
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:02,450
And they only stopped when
I decided to slow down

211
00:08:02,450 --> 00:08:05,020
by going back to golf
and doing more fun things

212
00:08:05,020 --> 00:08:07,210
like whitewater rafting with my son.

213
00:08:07,210 --> 00:08:08,890
I've also climbed Mount Snowden

214
00:08:08,890 --> 00:08:12,053
as well as going on the
fastest zip-line in Europe.

215
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:14,553
Believe it or not,

216
00:08:14,553 --> 00:08:16,880
these things keep me
relaxed and enjoying life,

217
00:08:16,880 --> 00:08:19,750
which means I can put
more effort into my work.

218
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:21,530
I now understand more than ever

219
00:08:21,530 --> 00:08:24,080
that a healthy body is a healthy mind.

220
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:26,240
There's a mountain of
evidence that suggests

221
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:29,630
a good night's sleep
seriously boosts productivity.

222
00:08:29,630 --> 00:08:33,050
One study of 4,188 US workers

223
00:08:33,050 --> 00:08:36,410
found significantly worse
productivity, performance,

224
00:08:36,410 --> 00:08:38,590
and safety outcomes among those

225
00:08:38,590 --> 00:08:40,520
that slept less than seven hours.

226
00:08:40,520 --> 00:08:42,800
That's why I now stopped working two hours

227
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:45,080
before going to bed without fail.

228
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:47,990
I'm trying to exercise more
by building my own gym.

229
00:08:47,990 --> 00:08:50,110
And I always try to eat healthy foods

230
00:08:50,110 --> 00:08:51,720
to boost my productivity.

231
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:54,470
The way I think of my
body is like a sports car.

232
00:08:54,470 --> 00:08:56,330
You won't fill with any old trash,

233
00:08:56,330 --> 00:08:59,150
you'd made sure everything
was top of the range.

234
00:08:59,150 --> 00:09:01,800
- [Narrator] What kind of
sports car are you dad?

235
00:09:01,800 --> 00:09:03,910
- I'm a Ferrari 355.

236
00:09:03,910 --> 00:09:06,320
Habit six, spending to receive.

237
00:09:06,320 --> 00:09:08,640
If you wanna become rich
it's highly unlikely

238
00:09:08,640 --> 00:09:10,210
you'll ever be able to achieve it

239
00:09:10,210 --> 00:09:13,100
without understanding
return on investment.

240
00:09:13,100 --> 00:09:17,510
If I purchase a product for
$50 and sell it for $75,

241
00:09:17,510 --> 00:09:20,210
my ROI is $25.

242
00:09:20,210 --> 00:09:23,720
50%, but the chances are,
you already knew that.

243
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:27,220
However, ROI stretches so
much further than profit

244
00:09:27,220 --> 00:09:28,600
on an item you're selling.

245
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:31,330
As a business owner, I
have multiple employees,

246
00:09:31,330 --> 00:09:34,130
and before making a
commitment to employ someone,

247
00:09:34,130 --> 00:09:37,730
I first have to work out exactly
how much this will cost me,

248
00:09:37,730 --> 00:09:39,400
and exactly how much money

249
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:42,130
I think that person will
generate for my business.

250
00:09:42,130 --> 00:09:44,660
Without calculating the
return on investment,

251
00:09:44,660 --> 00:09:46,360
I would never be able to determine

252
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:49,540
whether hiring an extra
employee is the right decision.

253
00:09:49,540 --> 00:09:51,200
Whether you're starting a business,

254
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:54,650
investing in the stock market,
or even just saving money,

255
00:09:54,650 --> 00:09:57,710
